									</div><!-- .comment-author .vcard -->

				
			</footer>

			<div class="comment-content"><p>Thanks for this excellent article about the application of Topic Modelling in Digital Humanities. </p>
<p>It seems that the equation for P(Z|W,D) should be divided by something like &#8220;total number of words in D + \alpha&#8221; to be a proper probability.</p>
</div>

